In[4]:
def clean_id(df, column):
    df[column] = df[column].astype(str).str.strip().str.upper()
    return df

demographics = clean_id(demographics, "CustomerID")
transactions = clean_id(transactions, "CustomerID")
service = clean_id(service, "CustomerID")
activity = clean_id(activity, "CustomerID")
churn = clean_id(churn, "CustomerID")

Merging Data

In[5]:
demographics = demographics.drop_duplicates(subset="CustomerID")
service = service.drop_duplicates(subset="CustomerID")
churn = churn.drop_duplicates(subset="CustomerID")

merged = demographics.copy()
merged = merged.merge(activity, on="CustomerID", how="left")
merged = merged.merge(churn, on="CustomerID", how="left")
In[6]:
# Transaction summary
txn_summary = transactions.groupby("CustomerID").agg(
    Num_Transactions=("TransactionID", "count"),
    First_Transaction_Date=("TransactionDate", "min"),
    Last_Transaction_Date=("TransactionDate", "max"),
    Total_Spent=("AmountSpent", "sum"),
    Avg_Spent=("AmountSpent", "mean"),
    Num_Product_Categories=("ProductCategory", "nunique")
).reset_index()
In[7]:
# Service summary
service_summary = service.groupby("CustomerID").agg(
    Num_Service_Interactions=("InteractionID", "count"),
    First_Interaction_Date=("InteractionDate", "min"),
    Last_Interaction_Date=("InteractionDate", "max"),
    Num_Interaction_Types=("InteractionType", "nunique"),
    Num_Resolved_Issues=("ResolutionStatus", lambda x: (x == "Resolved").sum()),
    Num_Unresolved_Issues=("ResolutionStatus", lambda x: (x != "Resolved").sum())
).reset_index()
In[8]:
merged = merged.merge(txn_summary, on="CustomerID", how="left")
merged = merged.merge(service_summary, on="CustomerID", how="left")

merged.fillna({
    "Num_Transactions": 0,
    "Num_Service_Interactions": 0,
    "Num_Interaction_Types": 0,
    "Num_Resolved_Issues": 0,
    "Num_Unresolved_Issues": 0,
    "Num_Product_Categories": 0,
    "Total_Spent": 0,
    "Avg_Spent": 0
}, inplace=True)
